Overview
This project is a web-based Tic-Tac-Toe game built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The game allows two players to play against each other on the same device. The design is simple and clean, ensuring a user-friendly experience.

Features
Interactive Gameplay: Players can click on the grid to place their marks (X or O).
Winning Logic: Determines the winner or a draw and displays the result.
Restart Game: Option to restart the game after it ends.
Responsive Design: Adapts to various screen sizes and devices.
Technologies Used
HTML5: For the structure of the web page.
CSS3: For styling and layout.
JavaScript: For game logic and interactivity.
HTML
The index.html file contains the structure of the web page, including the game board and control buttons.
CSS
The styles.css file includes the following:

Base Styles: Basic styling for body, headings, buttons, etc.
Layout: Flexbox for centering the game board and elements.
Responsive Design: Media queries to adjust the layout for different screen sizes.
JavaScript
The script.js file includes:

Game Logic: JavaScript functions to handle the game state, player turns, and winning conditions.
Event Listeners: JavaScript to manage clicks on the game board and restart button.
